New polling shows that one in three Americans blamed unusual winter temperatures on Earth's changing climate.
Similarly, 70 percent of those Americans who reported higher-than-usual temperatures this year blamed those usually mild conditions on climate change.
Of course, people's prior beliefs about climate change seem to color their perceptions of how weird was the winter weather.
Yet President Trump is pointing to the low thermometer reading as a sign that man-made climate change is not happening.
“I always thought climate change was a bunch of nonsense,” one Trump-supporting North Carolinian told The Post's Tracy Jan last year.